data.title: Treaty of Frankfurt - Vocab, Definition, and Must Know Facts
data.meta_description: The Treaty of Frankfurt refers to the peace agreement signed in 1871 between France and Germany, marking the end of the Franco-Prussian War. Under this treaty, France was forced to cede Alsace and part of Lorraine to Germany.
data.text:
Definition

The Treaty of Frankfurt refers to the peace agreement signed in 1871 between France and Germany, marking the end of the Franco-Prussian War. Under this treaty, France was forced to cede Alsace and part of Lorraine to Germany.
